RrUe1U5cWR9eFeXfc-Ty41YVow_6NQRMMr5QnR1wib9nqHmM6R73mO3rTxdbmmWo8A3560CcERTHVOtIEiUImnqqaQPPIffv5FYjrjeYrKcLcGkBMpF1DlTVBGiQMhocloYkxSJ9Bk-WWlC47pm5_4Cz4nXYyg1T5so-rFDRsk5MR64gAapf6TDkr1ooTXtt9WUi81GvqTNNNyeOMG7oCD7r6ejXFt2CkoDUbdjHieXAhtTgaTSHZGz_NE0MlaW04MyO9JZW22C4MsFjnrAcnahTG8wE_uUaPdkCLAqzgmRhe8ZRk4BFDE5BxjHmErNWxfkrrrkc5A3wtN2ZxB_27n3U-Ckf2AUR9QxnHgsUsHwsAzVmKbeVsvTRwOcITWN0m7gNC8HmKTuIwNKIeehxJTTPR967FQmbYAua8MY_SN4VmDm67N1-xF1MKUMS3LLOD8CX__JgVcjL4KstaOY0-4Nr_ZJQ0MR28uE6K_kvY2oCYeD-NuI=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering stored procedures in Spring Data JPA**\\n\\nI need to create an alias in H2 before making any calls, specifically using the `@Procedure` annotation in Spring Data JPA. I can define a static Java method in my test class, then use a DataSource to execute the alias creation. But I'm unsure if the JPA expects the stored procedure output differently. H2 supports callable statements and I might need an output parameter for my method. I'm also considering how to instantiate DTOs with constructor expressions in Spring Data JPA!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring JPQL queries**\\n\\nI'm considering the JPQL `@Query` with a `select new ...` statement or possibly using a derived query with a specific return type. It's interesting how both approaches work and how they can be utilized for fetching data efficiently. I wonder if I need to clarify which method is best for my situation or if one would provide better performance than the other. There’s a lot to think about regarding the return types and their implications on the repository layer!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering repository methods and EntityManager**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how each repository method has its own transaction, but I'm curious if the entity manager can be accessed per application. It seems like the Spring shared EntityManager proxy creates a new EntityManager for each method call. That might help ensure that the context remains isolated, but I wonder if this approach has any performance implications? I'll need to look into that more to understand the full picture.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0Z4CPRj8XJiVLuvASWIaUxkq|fc_0ac23e3825a28a730169ff3edb380c81a18fd003a8a547830c", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.data/spring-data-jpa/2.7.18/src/test/java/org_springframework_data/spring_data_jpa/Spring_data_jpaTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import javax.persistence.EntityListeners;\nimport javax.persistence.EntityManagerFactory;\n", "newText": "import javax.persistence.EntityManagerFactory;\n"}, {"oldText": "import javax.persistence.OneToMany;\nimport javax.persistence.Table;\n", "newText": "import javax.persistence.OneToMany;\nimport javax.persistence.PostLoad;\nimport javax.persistence.PostPersist;\nimport javax.persistence.Table;\nimport javax.persistence.Transient;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.data.annotation.CreatedBy;\nimport org.springframework.data.annotation.CreatedDate;\nimport org.springframework.data.annotation.LastModifiedBy;\nimport org.springframework.data.annotation.LastModifiedDate;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.AuditorAware;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.Example;\n", "newText": "import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.Example;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.springframework.data.domain.PageRequest;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.Sort;\n", "newText": "import org.springframework.data.domain.PageRequest;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.Persistable;\nimport org.springframework.data.domain.Sort;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.JpaSort;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.Specification;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.support.AuditingEntityListener;\n", "newText": "import org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.JpaSort;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.domain.Specification;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Modifying;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaAuditing;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;\n", "newText": "import org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Modifying;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.Query;\nimport org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.config.EnableJpaRepositories;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void auditingCallbacksPopulateCreationAndModificationMetadata() {\n        try (AnnotationConfigApplicationContext context =\n                new AnnotationConfigApplicationContext(JpaTestConfiguration.class)) {\n            JpaAuditedDocumentRepository repository = context.getBean(JpaAuditedDocumentRepository.class);\n            MutableAuditorAware auditorAware = context.getBean(MutableAuditorAware.class);\n\n            auditorAware.setCurrentAuditor(\"creator\");\n            JpaAuditedDocument saved = repository.saveAndFlush(new JpaAuditedDocument(\"initial title\"));\n\n            assertThat(saved.getCreatedBy()).isEqualTo(\"creator\");\n            assertThat(saved.getLastModifiedBy()).isEqualTo(\"creator\");\n            assertThat(saved.getCreatedAt()).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(saved.getLastModifiedAt()).isNotNull();\n\n            auditorAware.setCurrentAuditor(\"editor\");\n            saved.setTitle(\"revised title\");\n            JpaAuditedDocument updated = repository.saveAndFlush(saved);\n\n            assertThat(updated.getTitle()).isEqualTo(\"revised title\");\n            assertThat(updated.getCreatedBy()).isEqualTo(\"creator\");\n            assertThat(updated.getLastModifiedBy()).isEqualTo(\"editor\");\n            assertThat(updated.getCreatedAt()).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(updated.getLastModifiedAt()).isNotNull();\n        }\n    }\n\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void persistableEntitiesUseApplicationProvidedNewStateWithAssignedIdentifiers() {\n        try (AnnotationConfigApplicationContext context =\n                new AnnotationConfigApplicationContext(JpaTestConfiguration.class)) {\n            JpaAssignedIdRecordRepository repository = context.getBean(JpaAssignedIdRecordRepository.class);\n\n            JpaAssignedIdRecord created = repository.saveAndFlush(\n                    new JpaAssignedIdRecord(\"external-document\", \"draft\"));\n            assertThat(created.getId()).isEqualTo(\"external-document\");\n            assertThat(created.isNew()).isFalse();\n\n            created.setDescription(\"published\");\n            JpaAssignedIdRecord updated = repository.saveAndFlush(created);\n\n            assertThat(updated.isNew()).isFalse();\n            assertThat(repository.count()).isEqualTo(1);\n            assertThat(repository.findById(\"external-document\"))\n                    .get()\n                    .extracting(JpaAssignedIdRecord::getDescription)\n                    .isEqualTo(\"published\");\n        }\n    }\n\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Configuration\n    @EnableTransactionManagement\n    @EnableJpaAuditing\n    @EnableJpaRepositories(basePackageClasses = Spring_data_jpaTest.class)\n", "newText": "    @Configuration\n    @EnableTransactionManagement\n    @EnableJpaRepositories(basePackageClasses = Spring_data_jpaTest.class)\n"}, {"oldText": "        @Bean\n        public MutableAuditorAware auditorAware() {\n            return new MutableAuditorAware();\n        }\n\n        @Bean\n        public PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager(EntityManagerFactory entityManagerFactory) {\n", "newText": "        @Bean\n        public PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager(EntityManagerFactory entityManagerFactory) {\n"}, {"oldText": "interface JpaAuditedDocumentRepository extends JpaRepository<JpaAuditedDocument, Long> {\n}\n\ninterface UsernameOnly {\n", "newText":